In this updated code, there is an additional variable called cooldownTime which indicates the remaining cooldown time between generations. Initially, it is set to 0.
When cooldownTime is greater than 0, it displays the cooldown time in seconds in the progress bar. When cooldownTime reaches 0, it displays the time passed since the generation started.
Elsewhere in your code, after triggering a generation, you can set the cooldownTime value to the desired cooldown duration in seconds. For example:

// Generate the image and set the cooldown time
